┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    FASTAPI BACKEND (Render)                  │
│  /agent/advice   /papertrade   /trade/real   /wallet        │
│  /x402/verify    /copytrading  /permissions  /conversation  │
└──────┬───────────────┬──────────────────┬───────────────────┘
       │               │                  │
       ▼               ▼                  ▼
┌──────────┐   ┌──────────────┐   ┌──────────────────────┐
│  Neon DB │   │  OpenRouter  │   │  Base Network (EVM)  │
│ (Postgres│   │ Claude/OSS   │   │  Smart Wallet        │
│  cloud)  │   │  via Tavily  │   │  USDC on Base        │
└──────────┘   └──────────────┘   └──────────────────────┘
                                           │
                                   MPesa On-Ramp
                                   (Transak/MoonPay)
```

---

## The Money Flow — How It All Connects

```
User loads wallet:
  MPesa/Card → On-ramp Service (Transak) → USDC on Base → User's Smart Wallet

User pays for premium advice:
  User's Base Wallet → x402 micro-payment (USDC) → Backend verifies → Premium unlocked

User executes real trade:
  User's Base Wallet → (bridge if needed) → Polymarket CLOB on Polygon
  ↑ Agent generates advice → AutoTradeEngine sends tx → No custody (funds go direct)

User paper trades:
  No money moves → Trade logged in Neon only
```

> [!NOTE]
> **No custody**: NORT never holds user funds. The smart wallet is the user's own on-chain wallet. When AutoTradeEngine executes, it constructs and signs a transaction from the user's wallet directly to Polymarket. NORT is just the interface.

